ANTHRAX, HUMAN & GOATS - INDONESIA (WEST NUSA TENGGARA, WEST JAVA) (02)
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Thu, 9 Jan 2003 07:27:59 +0200
From: Dr. S. Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON [edited]
<http://www.GideonOnline.com>

[Some background figures on anthrax in Indonesia with moderator
comments/additions. -Mod.MHJ]
Human anthrax:
Year / number of cases
1989 / 89 [FAO had reported 25]
1992 / 88 cases
1993 / 136
1994 / 127
1995 / 79 (6 fatal)
1996 / 17
1997 / 13
42 cases (4 fatal) were reported in E. Nusa Tenggara during 1992 to 1996;
an outbreak of 268 suspect cases (one fatal) associated with ingestion of
buffalo meat was reported in Flores in 1999; [there were human cases
reported in 2000 but numbers are not available - Mod.MHJ];
[2001 / 22]
An outbreak of 5 cases of cutaneous anthrax associated with an infected cow
was reported in Bogor (West Java) in 2002; [plus 8 died after eating goat
meat in Doringu Village, Bima, Sumbara, West Nusa Tenggara; and latterly 7
sick in Bogor, West Java, after also eating goat meat.- Mod.MHJ]
Zoonotic infection:
Enzootic anthrax is reported from W. Java, C. Java, Jambi, W. Nusa
Tenggara, E. Nusa Tenggara, C. Sulawesi, S. Sulawesi, S.E. Sulawesi and
Irian Jaya; [also W. Sumatra, DKI Jakarta, and before independence it was
known in East Timor.]
[70 ovine-caprine anthrax in 1988];
1991 / 501
1992 / 19
1993 / 11
1994 / 8
1995 / 11
1996 / 11
1998 / 17
2000 / 19
[missing years mean little, as annual reporting to OIE is not consistent. -
Mod.MHJ]
252 cases of swine anthrax were reported in 1988 (including an epizootic in
Central Kupang which affected 40 pigs); 74 in 1991; 38 in 1996; [1998
outbreak reported in ProMEDmail involving Central Kupang].
[19 buffalo in 1992]; 380 cases of buffalo anthrax were reported in 1996;
[and a single case in 1999.]
Anthrax was identified in an imported ostrich in West Java in 2000; [whole
flock was destroyed.]
An outbreak of bovine anthrax in 1988 affected 4106 cattle;
1991 / 309
1992 / 41
1993 / 15
1994 / 10
1995 / 5
1996 / 72
1997 / 9
[1998 / 17]
--
Steve Berger
GIDEON
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
